# API Contract (Mandatory)

All API work must follow one shared contract across frontend and backend.

## Base path and versioning

- Use versioned REST paths under `/api/v1` unless explicitly documented otherwise.
- Breaking changes require a versioning plan in API docs.

## JSON conventions

- Use consistent JSON key casing across all endpoints.
- Use ISO 8601 UTC timestamps for date-time values.
- Represent money consistently for all endpoints (same format everywhere).
- Keep identifiers stable and documented (`id` type and format per resource).

## Request conventions

- Validate path params, query params, and body at the boundary layer.
- For list endpoints, standardize query keys: `page`, `limit`, `sort`, `order`, and filters.
- Document allowed ranges for pagination and default values.

## Response conventions

- Success payload shape must be predictable per resource.
- Use consistent pagination metadata for list endpoints.
- Use documented HTTP status semantics consistently (`200`, `201`, `204`, `400`, `401`, `403`, `404`, `409`, `422`, `500`).

## Change management

- Endpoint contract changes must be reflected in `backend/docs/api/*` in the same PR.
- Frontend DTOs must be updated to mirror documented request/response shapes.
